<TITLE> Germany increases Afghan troops </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 GERMANEY, Jan 26 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)---Chancellor Angela Merkel announces an increase of 500 troops for the German contingent in Afghanistan. Germany is set to raise its troop count in Afghanistan. Chancellor Angela Merkel announced that an extra 500 soldiers would be sent to help train Afghan security forces. A further 350 troops will be freed up as a "flexible reserve". Merkel also said she hoped Afghan authorities would be able to assume control of their own security by 2014. (SOUNDBITE) (German) GERMAN CHANCELLOR ANGELA MERKEL, SAYING: "I have never said that it will be an easy task. But I think that we can only really start thinking about withdrawing troops if we use more training and better protection of the population to create the conditions for stability." Germany already has over 4,000 troops stationed in Afghanistan. The government's come under pressure from the US and NATO to further increase its military presence. But the Defence Ministry has ruled out an even larger increase in a conflict which is highly unpopular among Germans. Global leaders will meet in London on Thursday where they're expected to agree a framework for the Afghan government to begin taking charge of secur
